From dbd82b930641cede8abf23876b28ff2e3d8c4fd3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Md Arif <111168803+sabamdarif@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 14:06:05 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] skip liblangtag teardown at exit on Android to avoid
 destroyed-mutex abort

LiblangtagDataRef's static destructor (libi18nlangtag) runs from
__cxa_finalize after libxml2's finalizer has already destroyed its
global mutexes. lt_db_finalize() frees liblangtag's XML documents via
libxml2, which locks such a mutex; Bionic FORTIFY aborts with
'pthread_mutex_lock called on a destroyed mutex' (SIGABRT tombstone:
libi18nlangtag -> liblangtag -> libxml2 -> abort in __cxa_finalize).
glibc tolerates this silently, Bionic does not. The abort also marks
the session as crashed, so every subsequent launch enters document
recovery. Teardown at process exit is only leak-checker tidiness;
skip it and let the kernel reclaim.
---
 i18nlangtag/source/languagetag/languagetag.cxx | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/i18nlangtag/source/languagetag/languagetag.cxx b/i18nlangtag/source/languagetag/languagetag.cxx
index 2b301efdb..89e7ad736 100644
--- a/i18nlangtag/source/languagetag/languagetag.cxx
+++ b/i18nlangtag/source/languagetag/languagetag.cxx
@@ -200,8 +200,10 @@ LiblangtagDataRef::LiblangtagDataRef()
 
 LiblangtagDataRef::~LiblangtagDataRef()
 {
+#if !defined(__ANDROID__)
     if (mbInitialized)
         teardown();
+#endif
 }
 
 void LiblangtagDataRef::setup()
-- 
2.55.0

